        <h1>LeetCode 788: Rotated Digits (C++)</h1>
        <div class="problem-description">
            <p><strong>Problem:</strong>
                An integer x is a good number if after rotating its digits 180 degrees, we get a valid and different
                number. When we rotate digits, 0 becomes 0, 1 becomes 1, 2 becomes 5, 5 becomes 2, 6 becomes 9, 9
                becomes 6, and digits 3, 4, 7 cannot be rotated. Find how many numbers between 1 and n (inclusive) are
                good numbers.
            </p>
            <p><strong>Example:</strong>
                Input: n = 10<br>
                Output: 4<br>
                Explanation: The numbers 2, 5, 6, 9 are good numbers (they are valid rotations). 1 is not good (rotates
                to itself). Numbers with 3, 4, 7 are invalid.
            </p>
        </div>
        <div class="code-container">
            <button class="copy-button" onclick="copyCode(this)">Copy Code</button>
            <pre><code class="language-cpp">class Solution {
public:
    bool isGoodNumber(int num) {
        bool hasInvalid = false, hasChange = false;
        while (num &gt; 0) {
            int digit = num % 10;
            if (digit == 3 || digit == 4 || digit == 7)
                hasInvalid = true; // makes number invalid
            if (digit == 2 || digit == 5 || digit == 6 || digit == 9)
                hasChange = true; // ensures number actually changes
            num /= 10;
        }
        if (hasInvalid) return false;
        return hasChange;
    }
    int rotatedDigits(int n) {
        int countGood = 0;
        for (int i = 1; i &lt;= n; i++) {
            if (isGoodNumber(i)) countGood++;
        }
        return countGood;
    }
};</code></pre>
